  "title": "FortiClient - Lack of client-side certificate validation in ZTNA service",
  "summary": "An improper certificate validation vulnerability [CWE-295] in FortiClientWindows, FortiClientLinux and FortiClientMac may allow a remote and unauthenticated attacker to perform a Man-in-the-Middle attack on the communication channel between the FortiGate and the FortiClient during the ZTNA tunnel creation",
